name: Mortal Kombat
description:
The day has finally come. You enter the arena, face to face with your mortal enemy. You've trained for this. Vengeance will be yours. What song is playing as you smash those combos and vanquish them?!

** Mortal Kombat theme not allowed **

name: Wet Hot American Summer
description: You've been working in the cafeteria kitchen of a summer camp from June to August. Your best friend is a can of peas. It's the last day of camp, but it might as well be your last day on Earth, because you'll never see your crush ever again. You'll need to transform into a whole new person before you can approach your crush, and you're going to need a kick ass song to inspire your transformation. May the eagles of Valhalla be with you, fellow campers!

name: King Shit
description: Today is the perfect day and everything is going your way. The sun is shining, the birds are chirping and every time you catch a glimpse of yourself you can't believe how awesome you look. Today, the world is moving at exactly your rhythm and you are radiating exuberance. There's a song exploding out of your chest and it's...

name: Conscious Uncoupling
description:
Not to be a bummer but all of the best songs are about breakups. Go for whatever vibe you want: crying on the bathroom floor, rebounding at the club, murdering your cheating husband, etc. 

In memory of Harry Styles and Olivia Wilde, may they rest in peace.

name: Longing for “You”
description:
You get to the party and see her across the room. She radiates light and goodness in a city full of vapid and uninspired girls. You knew she would be here, You know everything about her, You're here to protect her. You're meant to be, even if she doesn't know it yet. You've been called a stalker before but, people just don't understand You. You're just one of the good guys that really CARES!

This song is playing as time stops and you replay your future lives together as you approach her.

name: xX_Teen Angst_Xx
description: Mom and dad will never understand

name: Love is Cringe
description: The corniest and truest love songz.

name: Esoteric Earworms
description:
Pick a song that scores as high as possible on both of these measures: 
1) Esoteric: a song no one else has heard before. It should be brand new to as many people as possible.
2. Earworm: A song that's catchy as fuck, even obnoxiously catchy. A song that gets stuck in your head for days and comes to mind easily, even if it's been years since you've actually listened to it.

name: Solidarity Forever
description:
Protest songs that make you feel something in your gut. You know something is wrong with the world and this song speaks to it perfectly. From the big energy Fuck toys that you’d play on the front lines to slower songs that highlight injustices through just your headphones, whichever cause you want new or old. Solidarity for all of it!

** Except for these songs. They’re all great but they are disqualified bc we can all do better. 
All Rage Against the Machines Songs
Fight the Power by Public Enemy
Fuck the police by NWA

name: The Beat Goes On
description: Songs where percussion and beat are the main character: bonus points for creative and unconventional instrumentation. From pop rock to rap to techno to esoteric instrumental tracks and everything in between. The only rule is this: the percussion has to drive and be interwoven throughout: an 8 minute solo in the later half of a song isn't it.

name: Extraterrestrial Dance Party
description:
It is 2005 and you're home alone in your room listening to your iPod on your boom box. A blue light renders you incapacitated and you are pulled up into an alien spaceship. You wake up to tied to a table and see them inspecting your boom box. The aux cord is still attached, THIS is your chance to escape. You must play an "other worldly/futuristic" song that will force the aliens into a feverish, uncontrollable dance so you can make your escape. 

Doesn't have to be from 2005.

name: Altered States
description:
You know ‘em by many names: Goofballs, Dusters, Blotters, Benzos, Beans, Black Beauties, Buttons, Biscuits, Skittles, Schoolboys, Snappers, Arnolds, Moon Rocks, Vickies, Footballs, Fizzies, Luudes, and Marijuana.

That’s right folks, we’re talkin about DRUGS! Let’s hear some tunes to get hi to, love letters to ‘llicit substances, trippy tracks, haunting ballads of addiction and regret, maybe even some roided-out jock jams?? Anything that makes you feel a certain kinda way

name: Blessed Union of Souls
description:
this is what you listen to alone. the stuff that you crave to listen to because your vibes are on the same frequency or it just syncs up with your insides

dark, intimate, bubbly, irreverent, really whatever

pick some music that may be kinda not chill to listen to with others. the weird shit that you like. 

put yourself out there! and maybe someone else here will dig it too

name: Ekphrastic Exercise
description:
Choose a song inspired by this image. Any way you go about choosing a song is fine - thinking about colors, narrative, historical moments - any and all interpretations are correct! Have fun!

https://tinyurl.com/4ubzca52

name: and the Jay-Z song was on...
description:
I’m looking for songs where musical artists talk about slash name drop other musical artists. 

This does not include “list” songs (like hot topic, we didn’t start the fire, end of the world as we know it etc. ) or features (rappers delight, any dj khaled song)

name: Let’s get onomatopoetic
description: Submit a song that features onomatopoeia in the lyrics
